FROM content_items
WHERE content_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
- 'Blossomed in the sunlight' refers to the content items having more than 100 views and 50 downloads;
- 'Video gems' refers to content items of the 'Video' type that are published and not archived;
- 'Audience's attention' refers to the number of views;
- 'Number of collectors' refers to the number of downloads;
- 'Rate at which they turned viewers into buyers' refers to the conversion rate;
- 'Total gold they have minted' refers to the total revenue generated from the product offers.

- "Engaging content" refers to content that has a high number of views and downloads;
- "Recently created content" is content with the latest `content_date`;
- "Conversion rate" is the percentage of users who take a desired action (e.g., making a purchase) after viewing the content;
- "Conversion rate vs. average" is the ratio of the content's conversion rate to the average conversion rate across all content;
- "Recent views" are views that occurred within the last 7 days.

- "Published" means the content is available to the public;
- "Not archived" means the content is still active and accessible;
- "Top 5 most viewed" refers to the highest number of views.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(*) AS view_count
FROM content_views
WHERE view_date >= '2023-06-01' AND view_date < '2023-06-02';

SELECT content_id, title, views, downloads
FROM content_items
ORDER BY views DESC;

external_knowledge:
- "content_date DESC" ensures that the most recently created or updated content is listed first;
- "log_views" is the logarithm of the views, used to normalize the scale of the number of views;
- "conversion_percentage" is the conversion rate expressed as a percentage.

sql:
SELECT title, views
FROM content_items
ORDER BY views DESC;

external_knowledge:
